status: MARC21-007: Tape width of sound recording

scope note (en): Nonprofessional, consumer, and some professional reels, and most 8-track cartridges use 1/4 in. tape.

definition (en): Item is not a tape or does not include a tape.
scope note (en): For example, if the item is a disc.
Recording studios customarily use 1/2 in. tape. Some 8-track cartridges have been issued in 1/2 in. tape.

definition (en): Recording studios often use 1 inch tape. Some 8-track cartridges have been issued in 1 in. tape.
scope note (en): Recording studios often use 1 inch tape. Some 8-track cartridges have been issued in 1 in. tape.

definition (en): Width other than 1/8 in., 1/4 in., 1/2 in., 1 in.
